<h3 id="while">while</h3>

<p>A while loop is given a parameter that evaluates to a boolean (remember, that‚Äôs just true or false). Once that boolean expression becomes false, the while loop is not executed again, and the program continues after the while loop.</p>

<h3 id="dowhile">do/while</h3>

<p>A do/while loop works in a similar way to a while loop; one important difference is that the code within the loop gets executed one time, prior to the conditional check to see if the code should be executed. In a ‚Äúdo/while‚Äù loop, the conditional check is placed at the end of the loop as opposed to the beginning</p>

